  "articleSummary": "The article argues that for cloud workloads demanding high I/O, Amazon’s EC2 i3 instance family (especially i3.large and larger) offers the best price‑to‑performance ratio because its native NVMe SSDs deliver up to 1 GB/s throughput at a relatively modest monthly cost. It supports this claim with head‑to‑head benchmark tables and price comparisons, noting that while network bandwidth often falls short of advertised “up to 10 Gb/s” speeds, the NVMe storage remains the dominant performance factor. The piece is written as a practical, data‑driven tutorial aimed at system administrators and developers evaluating cloud providers, using a straightforward “TL;DR” framing and occasional metaphor of “ultra‑fast” hardware to emphasize speed advantages.",
